### System:
You are an AI assistant that follows instruction extremely well. Help as much as you can.

### User:
what are the verb tenses?

### Response:


The following is a list of common English verb tenses, along with examples for each one: 
Present Tense - I walk to school every day. (present continuous) 
Past Simple - Yesterday, we went to the park. (past simple) 
Past Continuous - They were playing soccer when I arrived. (past continuous) 
Future Simple - Tomorrow, I will go shopping after work. (future simple) 
Present Perfect Tense - She has already eaten dinner. (present perfect) 
Past Perfect Tense - He had finished his homework before he went to bed. (past perfect) 
Future Perfect Tense - By tomorrow night, we will have completed our project. (future perfect)
